Uses of Package
udel.GardenProject.plants

  • Packages that use udel.GardenProject.plants 
    Package Description
    udel.GardenProject.garden
    All the critical code that brings the application together and runs it.
    udel.GardenProject.plants
    Contains the Plant class that stores all the information that can be obtained by the PlantLoader, and Comparators to sort the a list of Plant objects for searching.
    udel.GardenProject.plotObjects
    Contains all the plot objects that can be placed on the Plot Designer.

    Placed within the main.udel.plants package as plants can also be placed on the Plot Designer.

    Has Buildings, Fences, Rivers, and other critical plot objects.

    NOTE: Everything in this package needs to implement the Serializable interface to be serialized by Model's save method when acting on the Session class.

    NOTE 2: Every class in this package and any subpackages must implement PlotObject or implement an abstract class that itself implements PlotObject at some point.
    udel.GardenProject.windows
    All the distinct windows that can be displayed to the user.
  • Classes in udel.GardenProject.plants used by udel.GardenProject.garden 
    Class and Description
    Plant
    For every plant, there is a corresponding Plant object that contains as much information that can be loaded by PlantLoader.

    Plant data was gathered from public domain sources using Python scripts, and the plant data is stored as .json files in main.udel.plants.data
